      <scopecontent id="aspace_cf9ff385af4763f8fb391a62e86fdea0">
         <head>Content Description</head>
         <p>Collection consists of 36 drawings created by Colin Rowe during his time as a student at Liverpool University School of Architecture between 1938 and 1942.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <userestrict id="aspace_d4fef3c261f5e6135b62c8f50d3cfbd1">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright has been transferred to Yale University for unpublished materials authored or otherwise produced by Colin Rowe. Copyright status for other collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.</p>
      </userestrict>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_6598bb1439236d0be19f025733a604ac">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The collection is open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0696ff9ff2d6589a9195984b3ff8ff20">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Colin Frederick Rowe, architecture historian, educator, and critic, was born in Rotherham, Yorkshire, England on March 27, 1920. Rowe entered Liverpool University School of Architecture in 1938. His studies were interrupted when he left to join the British Infantry in 1942. Returning home after sustaining serious injury, Colin Rowe completed a MA in Architectural History at the Warburg Institute in 1945 and studied at Yale University under a Fulbright Scholarship in 1952. Early in his career, Rowe taught at various institutions, before settling in at Cornell University retiring after more than 30 years as Andrew Dickson White Professor of Architecture in 1990.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_ca31f345fd393da4fb0996881acc4c69">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Colin Rowe papers (ARCH 0001). Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library Special Collections, Yale University.</p>
      </prefercite>
